# 🧱 Code Example

Example: Launching EC2 instance using CLI

```bash
# AWS CLI configure karna (credentials set karna)
aws configure

# EC2 instance create karna
aws ec2 run-instances \
--image-id ami-123456 \
--instance-type t3.micro \
--count 1 \
--key-name prod-key \
--security-group-ids sg-123456 \
--subnet-id subnet-123456

# EC2 instances ki list check karna
aws ec2 describe-instances
```

Explanation:

* `aws configure` → AWS credentials configure kar raha hai
* `run-instances` → naya server create kar raha hai
* `instance-type` → server ka size define kar raha hai
* `describe-instances` → running servers ki list dikhata hai

